value.title: Hunter Biden brought VP Joe to dinner with shady business partners
value.excerpt: Joe Biden met with Ukrainian, Russian and Kazakhstani business associates of his son’s at a dinner in Washington, DC, while he was vice president, records on Hunter Biden’s abandoned laptop show.

value.title: Trump Organization probe enters potentially ominous phase with grand jury convened
value.excerpt: Special grand jury marks a shift in Cy Vance's Trump Organization probe as possible evidence of criminal conduct may be presented.

value.title: Trump, Patriots owner Robert Kraft accused of trying to influence late senator's Spygate probe: report
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump and New England Patriots owner Robert Kraft were accused in a new report Wednesday of trying to influence the investigation into the team’s 2007 Spygate scandal.

value.title: Trump asks court to toss out Capitol assault suit from Eric Swalwell
value.excerpt: Swalwell is suing Mr. Trump, Donald Trump Jr., GOP Congressman Mo Brooks of Alabama and Rudy Giuliani, the former president's lawyer, over the events of January 6.

value.excerpt: A hard-charging United States senator from Pennsylvania named Arlen Specter had launched an investigation into the Spygate scandal. value.title: Biden to nominate LA Mayor Eric Garcetti as ambassador to India: report
value.excerpt: President Biden reportedly plans to nominate Los Angeles Mayor Eric Garcetti as the next U.S. ambassador to India.

value.title: Kamala Harris urged by New Mexico GOP lawmaker to involve Congress in her ‘root causes’ talks
value.excerpt: Vice President Kamala Harris should consult members of Congress as she continues discussions with Mexican and Central American officials on the "root causes" of migration, a Republican lawmaker urged this week.

value.excerpt: Republican former President Donald Trump on Tuesday night said he "usually did the opposite" of what infectious diseases expert Dr. Anthony Fauci advised during his presidency. value.title: Trump: ‘It was obvious to smart people’ COVID came from Wuhan lab
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump claimed in a Newsmax interview that “it was obvious to smart people” that COVID-19 emerged from a lab in the Chinese city of Wuhan.

value.title: Lawrence Jones slams President Biden for failing to deliver on promise to 'heal' America: 'Where are we now?'
value.excerpt: "Fox News Primetime" host Lawrence Jones ripped Joe Biden and Democrats Tuesday for their lack of urgency in solving America’s policing problem and not addressing the real issues facing Black America.

value.title: Trump blasts reported grand jury, says part of ‘greatest Witch Hunt’
value.excerpt: The 45th president claimed the grand jury probe is an extension of the Russia investigation that plagued his administration for two years.

value.title: Pentagon official leading military extremism crackdown said Trump supporters are extremists
value.excerpt: The Pentagon official tasked with leading efforts to crack down on extremist views among military servicemembers once asserted that supporters of former President Donald Trump were also supporters of racism, misogyny and extremism.

value.title: Biden to travel to Oklahoma to commemorate 100th anniversary of Tulsa race massacre
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden will visit Tulsa, Oklahoma, next week in honor of the 100th anniversary of the Tulsa race massacre, the White House announced on Tuesday.

value.title: Biden defends decision not to sanction company building controversial Russian gas pipeline
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden on Tuesday stood by his decision not to sanction the company in charge of building Russia's Nord Stream 2 gas pipeline, characterizing the move as protecting relationships with European allies.

value.title: Trump's hold on GOP remains as he teases Texas AG endorsement
value.excerpt: As Donald Trump seeks to remain a kingmaker in Republican politics, the former President teased an upcoming endorsement in an important statewide race in Texas.

value.title: 'The clock is ticking': Democrats grow restless with Biden's infrastructure talks as Republicans float next counteroffer
value.excerpt: With sides still far apart, some Democrats say the time is nearing for Biden to try to pass an infrastructure package without Republicans.

value.title: Trump teases endorsement in Texas AG race
value.excerpt: Former President Trump on Tuesday said he would soon announce his endorsement in the Texas Attorney General race.

value.title: Nikki Haley calls for Beijing Olympics boycott, urges Biden diplomats to create COVID probe alliance
value.excerpt: Former U.S. Ambassador to the United Nations Nikki Haley on Tuesday called on the United States to boycott the 2022 Winter Olympics set to take place next February in Beijing.

value.title: Face to face: June summit for Biden, Putin as tensions rise
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden and Russia’s Vladimir Putin agreed Tuesday to meet next month in Geneva, a face-to-face encounter the White House hopes will help bring some predictability to a fraught relationship that’s only worsened in the first months of the Democratic administration.

value.title: George Floyd’s family meets with Biden, Harris on anniversary of his death
value.excerpt: The family of George Floyd met with President Biden and Vice President Kamala Harris Tuesday, on the anniversary of Floyd’s death, and demanded police reform be passed.

value.title: Biden says U.S. sanctions against Belarus are in play
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden said on Tuesday that U.S. sanctions against Belarus are in play, but declined to offer more details.

value.title: Steve Bannon’s Indictment Dismissed After Fight With Prosecutors Over Trump Pardon’s Reach
value.excerpt: A federal judge dismissed an indictment against former Trump adviser Steve Bannon, declining an unusual request by prosecutors to keep the fraud charges in place despite a presidential pardon.

value.title: Biden administration moves forward with plan to bring offshore wind to California coast for the first time
value.excerpt: The Biden administration announced Tuesday that it is moving to advance offshore wind power on the coast of California for the first time. When developed, the regions selected have the potential to generate enough green energy for up to 1.6 million homes over the next decade, according to the administration.
